title: Iraqi Election Could Determine the Future for U.S. Forces in the Country
sub_head: Many younger Iraqis are protesting instead of voting in an election they see as unlikely to prompt change
body:
BAGHDAD—Iraqis are voting in a parliamentary election that could shape the future for U.S. forces still based there and indicate how Baghdad will navigate a broader geopolitical power struggle between Washington and Tehran.
Sunday’s election, which was brought forward as a concession to a protest movement that began in 2019, is dominated by the issues that triggered the upswell of dissent: an economic crisis and endemic corruption.
